fields.description:
Classic Eames design, the 670 lounge chair and 671 ottoman for Herman Miller.
Rosewood paneled and black leather upholstery, ottoman is stamp 1979
Great shape over all for its age, light signs of normal wear.

John Keal for Brown Saltman Mahogany Sideboard
Two cabinets, with two shelves, four drawers, not shown in photos all the way on it’s bottom there’s a
long cabinet that would hold the table’s leaves.
Condition, fair/good. Great bones, would need to be refinished to really bring out it’s beauty.
Made with navy Irish linen, this item has a beautiful goldenrod applique and magenta trim. Adds style to most any living room.

These occasional tables, designed by Ayush Kasliwal, in hand-turned ebonized Beech wood or Teak, combine traditional ornamented furniture elements, deconstructs them, and recombines them in a contemporary form.

Wefts of horsehair are combined with brass and etched glass, implying a structural weight bearing function for the coarse hair. Pretty funky!

Lamping: 2 Type A T10 bulbs. Max 60W each. 25W bulbs included. All pieces made to order.
If you're going to get double crossed, we hope it is because you got this lamp. Black glaze with harness detail, don't worry it's a chic and trustworthy piece.

It's all about geometry. or was it trigonometry? These fixtures are a study in repeating triangular and conical shapes. Made with blackened brass and hand cast porcelain cones to emit a delicate glow. Made to order.

This Mitchell Black piece fits in with our philosophy --- make a nod to the past, but focus on the present. This is a beautiful mix of traditional art and contemporary style. Used as table or wall art, this piece has an acrylic frame with brushed aluminum standoffs.

Striking like sunset in the Arizona desert. Each piece is dyed, painted, and printed by hand. This is art that you can interact with, objects that function while bringing style and warmth into any room. Proudly made in Los Angeles by Rule of Three.
Picture frame from Alexandra Von Furstenberg, the queen of acrylic decor. Place your photo between the two sheets of acrylic and then snap them together. What a snap to use!
You don't have to be a mad scientist to love this cluster vase. Made from an assemblage of smaller bottles, this piece allows you to emphasize the beauty of each flower.
A beautifully hand-crafted queen bed build from sustainably harvested and reclaimed woods, so every piece is one of a kind. Bring character to your bedroom, using this piece as a natural focal point.
This hand-crafted piece was built from exotic demolition hardwoods. It features a patchwork surface, balancing urban aesthetic with sustainable design. You can't get cooler than that.
This is an update on midcentury modern, with tailored box cushions and slim, tapered legs... and if you haven't gotten the memo yet, midcentury modern is so in.
A beautiful mix of iron and steel that features an antique nickel finish.
With its rounded high back and swiveling base, have you ever seen anything so smooth? Only a limited amount in stock.
Built from reclaimed pine and accented with a cool blue tone, this is definitely not run of the mill.
Sleep in style in this Art Deco inspired bed. Sleek, linear design married with modern upholstery details makes this a perfect piece for any contemporary bedroom.
Simple yet sophisticated, this full trundle bed will bring a modern aesthetic and distinct style to your bedroom.
Made from vintage textile spools, this wine rack's a showstopper.

The Bihar reminds us of our travels to India, the beautiful colors and hand block printed fabrics. However, these headboards are handmade by craftman in the USA. But, they'll still inspire you to dream about your future travels.
Inspired by a european design from the 1960's, this handwoven chair is rustic yet chic. (Note: decorating your space in all things wood is not required).
Don't be square. This handsome hexagon-shaped table is made from a solid chunk of mango wood. The top is covered in antique brass foil to create a subtle contrast in color and texture.
Standard design with a splash of personality. Now, just cue up a rerun of ER for the full Clooney experience.
A perfect antique style linen cabinet made with reclaimed wood and iron. Great for creating an old rustic charm into your home decor.
Combines modern functionality with woods reclaimed from former buildings. (oh, If that wood could talk, the stories it would tell). Anyway can't you just picture this in a designer loft in Brooklyn?

Artist Dana Hemenway takes macrame to a whole new level with these limited edition woven extension cord lights. These unique pieces are visually playful. They add a pop to any room.

Available in custom colors and lengths. These are made to order.
If you're looking for a traditional yet unique statement piece, search no more. This beaded chandelier features impressive metalwork design in its intricate cascades of iron chains. So classy.

Whimsical and oh so fantastical. This is what fairy tales are made of... or maybe what eco-friendly homes are made of. Regardless, remember it's okay to have a few daring pieces. It's all about how you put it together.
Test

Leftovers will make you swoon! Receiving 3-5 deliveries a day, you never know what vintage gems will come in through the door. If you're looking for unique and ever-changing eye candy, Leftovers in the place!

Past Perfect is a world renowned antique, vintage and modern collective. Operated by 30 plus independent dealers, you're sure to find something special. Past Perfect carries a range of items, from mid-century modern to antique. New items arrive daily.

Cavalier is a destination for seekers of all that is uncommon and collected. True to a code that celebrates all that is singular and luxurious, Cavalier showcases carefully curated new, vintage and bespoke pieces. It is the exclusive source for interior designer Jay Jeffers’ debut collection of California‐made furniture, as well as the sole stockist for a limited‐edition selection of home furnishings and accessories created in partnership with designers from around the world.

This store was made for home decor addicts. Stop by and see their ever changing room displays, updated daily. You'll truly find one-of-a-kind inspiration for your room or a solution to any design challenge.

Harrington Galleries is a lifestyle emporium has been a Bay Area landmark for more than 40 years. Specializing in estate liquidation, they sell antiques and vintage furniture. These items are complimented by carefully selected new furniture items... mixing the best of the old with the best of the new.

Big Daddy’s Antiques is a retailer of one-of-a-kind antiques and reproductions from European, Asian, and North American markets. Whether you are looking for that funky one-of-a-kind antique piece, looking to create your own unique piece, or seeking an eclectic location for your next event, Big Daddy’s is the place to be.

Every piece we find is a chance to learn about and appreciate a designer or artist that created a beautiful moment in history - moments that we can all fill our homes and work spaces with to create environments full of sculptural lines, rich tones, and unique details

The name Ohmega is derived from the greek symbol omega, signifying rebirth, and 'ohm's law', the measure of electrical resistance. Ohmega Salvage  builds community through commerce by being a model of reuse, recycling and social exchange.

Zinc Details is an independently owned showroom, gallery, modern design authority and essential resource for the San Francisco creative community since 1991. Zinc Details assembles an exuberant mix of art, design and craft that is expertly curated from sources around the globe.
Carousel Consignment has a love and flair for circus and all things vintage. They have collected vintage/antique furniture, art, and decor for years, with a fervor bordering on obsession.
